<br>
Large damage shields are very effective but the problem with a mage has using pets with the pets with the large DS is keeping the pet alive.  With your cleric, you have mana efficient healing so that should not be a problem.  <br>
<br>
a.  I would first try the 49 Fire Pet.  I would summon Armour, focus items, and weapons to up its AC and Hit Points.  The problem with this pet is its low HP but with your clerics buffs and healing it might be enough.  <br>
<br>
b.  I would also try a MS II pet that fireshields itself.  You might have to cast several to get one that fireshields itself.  Again fully buff the pet with everything.  This pet has larger HP and damage mitigation than the fire pet but you give up its fire attack but gain extra melee attacks.  <br>
<br>
c.  I would also try the 53 air pet.  It will be the best tank especially with the cleric's buffs.  It is the easiest pet to control.  It does more damage than the earth pet.  It has the best taunt.  The only problem is it will be missed more than the earth pet and won't do as much damage through the DS.  <br>
<br>
At 56, Dyzil's Deafening Decoy becomes an option.  It is basically the 49th Fire pet with an additional AE taunt.  It should hold aggro really well, just might be to mana intensive to keep alive.  <br>
<br>
If you do test these pets, please report back as to which one you thought were useful.  <br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Dabrighter Mage of the 53 level.<br>
